canonical:
  title: 賀皇太子箋
  author: 卞季良
  language: lzh
  text: 重華協帝端居貳極之尊申命自天屢致禎符之現瞻聆所及懽忭惟均云云偉量淵冲英姿玉裕功益隆於翊亮物並臻於嘉祥慈烏馴象之鮮明天生上瑞浙江淝河之感應民獲安居醴泉涵甘露之凝空花映圓光之照此皆稀有之景貺實爲太平之昭徵謹當邈處荒陬幸逢盛際阻參趨蹌之列倍申頌禱之勤
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 賀皇太子箋
  author: 卞季良
  language: lzh
  text: 重華協帝。端居貳極之尊。申命自天。屢致禎符之現。瞻聆所及。懽忭惟均。云云。偉量淵冲。英姿玉裕。功益隆於翊亮。物並臻於嘉祥。慈烏馴象之鮮明。天生上瑞。浙江淝河之感應。民獲安居。醴泉涵甘露之凝。空花映圓光之照。此皆稀有之景貺。實爲太平之昭徵。謹當邈處荒陬。幸逢盛際。阻參趨蹌之列。倍申頌禱之勤。
korean:
  title: 하 황태자 전
  author: 변계량
  language: kor
  text: 중화(重華 황태자)께서 황제를 도우시어 단정히 이극(貳極)의 높은 위에 계시옵고, 하늘로부터 신명(申命)이 내리시어 번번이 상서가 나타나오니, 보고 듣는 자마다 기뻐하고 춤춤이 고르도소이다. 운운. 크신 도량이 연못처럼 깊으시고 영명(英明)하신 자태가 옥같이 너그러우시며, 공(功)이 더욱 익량(翊亮)에 높으시어 만물이 아울러 가상(嘉祥)에 이르오니, 자애(慈愛)로운 까마귀와 순한 코끼리가 분명히 하늘이 낸 상서(上瑞)였삽고, 절강(浙江)ㆍ비하(淝河)의 감응(感應)으로 백성들이 안거(安居)를 얻었사오며, 예천(醴泉)에 감로(甘露)가 엉기고 공중의 꽃이 원광(圓光)을 비치는 등, 이것들이 모두 희한한 큰 선물이오니 실로 태평의 밝은 징조이옵나이다. 삼가 마땅히 □멀리 구석진 고장에 살면서 다행히 성시(盛時)를 만났사옴에 추창하는 열(列)에는 참가하지 못하오나, 곱절로 송도(頌禱)의 충성을 퍼옵나이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0350_010_0730&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: A Memorial Presented to the Crown Prince
  author: Byeon Gye-ryang
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The Crown Prince of Reborn Glory assists the Emperor, dwelling serene in the dignity of second rank. Celestial mandate descends from Heaven, manifesting auspicious signs in succession. All who witness and hear rejoice in equal measure. And so forth.

    Vast is your wisdom, deep as a fathomless pool. Radiant your bearing, generous as jade. Your merit ever rises in support of the throne, as all things converge upon blessings. The compassionate raven and the gentle elephant—these are Heaven's own portents made manifest. The Zhejiang and Fei rivers respond in kind, granting the people peace and settled homes. Sweet dew crystallizes upon the Auspicious Spring; celestial blossoms cast their perfect light upon the void. These are all rare and wondrous gifts, true harbingers of great peace.

    Humble and remote is my dwelling place, yet fortune grants me to witness this golden age. Though I cannot join the ranks of those who personally pay homage, I offer doubly my fervent prayers and praise.
  footnotes:
    - The Crown Prince of Reborn Glory (重華) alludes to the legendary sage-king Yao, also known as Yao of Reborn Glory.
    - The manifestations mentioned—the compassionate raven, the gentle elephant, sweet dew at the Auspicious Spring—are classical Chinese omens signifying virtuous rulership and cosmic harmony.
    - The Zhejiang and Fei rivers were significant waterways believed to reflect Heaven's approval through propitious phenomena.
